{"lemma":"إِعْصارِ","slug":"إِعْصارِ","root":"ع.ص.ر","root_slug":"ع-ص-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"إِعْصار","root":"عصر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29328"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عَصْر (ʕaṣr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عِصْر (ʕiṣr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عُصْر (ʕuṣr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عُصُر (ʕuṣur)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29328","headword_ar":"اـِعْصَارٌ","root":"ESr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A whirlwind of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a pillar; a wind that raises dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the sky and the earth, and revolves, resembling a pillar; called also by the Arabs a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawobaEap","text_ar":"زَوْبَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of the masc. gender; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that raises the dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rises towards the sky, as though it were a pillar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that blows from the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and raises the dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rises"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a pillar towards the sky;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called by the people a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawobaEap","text_ar":"زَوْبَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) unless it blow in this manner, with vehemence, it is not thus called: (Zj, TA:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamuwdN","text_ar":"عَمُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that rises into the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind that raises the clouds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with thunder and lightning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) mentioned in the Kur ii. 268: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAr","text_ar":"عِصَار","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or this latter word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust raised into the air, by the wind, in the form of a pillar"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA EaSarato bihi","text_ar":"مَا عَصَرَتْ بِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu mina Alt~uraAbi fiY AlhawaA='i","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ مِنَ التُّرَابِ فِى الهَوَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSarN","text_ar":"عَصَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaASiyru","text_ar":"اَعَاصِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaASiru","text_ar":"اَعَاصِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[occurring in poetry]. (Ham p. 678.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino kunota","text_ar":"اـِنْ كُنْتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHFA faqado laAqayota A_iEoSaArFA","text_ar":"رِيحًا فَقَدْ لَاقَيْتَ اـِعْصَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou be a wind, thou hast met with a whirlwind of dust like a pillar"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov. of the Arabs, (O, TA,) relating to a man in whom is somewhat of power and who meets with one superior to him, (O,) or to a man who meets his adversary with courage. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEoduhu A_iEoSaArN","text_ar":"وَعْدُهُ اـِعْصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His promising is"},{"kind":"text","text":"unprofitable like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a whirlwind of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Zj","AZ","S","O","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}